ibSmMIB.description: The managed objects for Infiniband Subnet Managers(SM).

IbSmVendorID.name: IbSmVendorID
IbSmVendorID.description: Device vendor ID, per IEEE. see www.standards.ieee.org/regauth/oui/oui.txt for details.

ibSmConfigTable.name: ibSmConfigTable
ibSmConfigTable.description: A table used to list all configured Subnet Managers on this node.

ibSmConfigSubnetPrefix.name: ibSmConfigSubnetPrefix
ibSmConfigSubnetPrefix.description: Subnet prefix of this IB subnet.

ibSmConfigSubnetGUID.name: ibSmConfigSubnetGUID
ibSmConfigSubnetGUID.description: PortGUID of the port where the SM resides.

ibSmConfigPriority.name: ibSmConfigPriority
ibSmConfigPriority.description: Assigned priority for this Subnet Manager. It is used as one of parameters in selecting the master Subnet Manager in an IB subnet.

ibSmConfigSMKey.name: ibSmConfigSMKey
ibSmConfigSMKey.description: SM_Key of the SM. SM Key exclusively identifies an SM on the subnet. User should take extra caution when setting this value.

ibSmConfigAdminSMState.name: ibSmConfigAdminSMState
ibSmConfigAdminSMState.description: Administrative state of the Subnet Manager.

ibSmConfigSMState.name: ibSmConfigSMState
ibSmConfigSMState.description: Subnet Manager's State: 0: notActive; 1: discovering; 2: standby; 3: master(3);

ibSmConfigActCount.name: ibSmConfigActCount
ibSmConfigActCount.description: Activity counter that increments each time the SM issues an SMP or performs other management activities. Used as a heartbeat indicator by standby SMs.

ibSmConfigStatus.name: ibSmConfigStatus
ibSmConfigStatus.description: Used to create or delete a row in this table. Creating a row has the effect of assigning a Subnet Manager to an IB subnet. Depending on the negotiation process the Subnet Manager can take the role of a master or standby Subnet Manager for the IB subnet. Deleting a row has the effect of removing the Subnet Manager from the IB subnet.

ibSmConfigSweepInterval.name: ibSmConfigSweepInterval
ibSmConfigSweepInterval.description: Used to configure the interval the SM should sweep the IB network. The value is specified in seconds.

ibSmConfigResponseTimeout.name: ibSmConfigResponseTimeout
ibSmConfigResponseTimeout.description: Used to configure the time-out interval for that SM should wait for a response before the SM declares a port to be unresponsive.

ibSmConfigPortAgingTime.name: ibSmConfigPortAgingTime
ibSmConfigPortAgingTime.description: Used to configure the time interval for that SM should retain a port's configuration after the port is unresponsive.

ibSmConfigMinUnicastLID.name: ibSmConfigMinUnicastLID
ibSmConfigMinUnicastLID.description: Used to configure unicast LID range for the Subnet Manager. This is the low limit of the LID and its value must be less than the value of ibSmConfigMaxUnicastLID.

ibSmConfigMaxUnicastLID.name: ibSmConfigMaxUnicastLID
ibSmConfigMaxUnicastLID.description: Used to configure unicast LID range for the Subnet Manager. This is the high limit of the LID and its value must be greater Than the value of ibSmConfigMinUnicastLID.

ibSmConfigDefaultLMC.name: ibSmConfigDefaultLMC
ibSmConfigDefaultLMC.description: Used to configure how many LID to be assigned per port. The user should take extra caution when setting this value because the change affects the routing of the packets and existing LID assignments.

ibSmConfigMasterPollInterval.name: ibSmConfigMasterPollInterval
ibSmConfigMasterPollInterval.description: Used to configure the time interval the Standby Subnet Manager will use to poll the Master Subnet Manager.

ibSmConfigMasterPollRetries.name: ibSmConfigMasterPollRetries
ibSmConfigMasterPollRetries.description: Used to configure the number of retries the Standby Subnet Manager will retry its poll of the Master Subnet Manager.

ibSmConfigMKeyLeasePeriod.name: ibSmConfigMKeyLeasePeriod
ibSmConfigMKeyLeasePeriod.description: Used to configure the MKey lease period.

ibSmNodeInfoTable.name: ibSmNodeInfoTable
ibSmNodeInfoTable.description: A table used to list all IB nodes that are actively managed by the Subnet Managers on this device.

ibSmNodeInfoSubnetPrefix.name: ibSmNodeInfoSubnetPrefix
ibSmNodeInfoSubnetPrefix.description: Subnet prefix of this IB subnet.

ibSmNodeInfoType.name: ibSmNodeInfoType
ibSmNodeInfoType.description: Type of node being managed: reserved(0), channelAdapter(1), switch(2), router(3),error(4).

ibSmNodeInfoNumPorts.name: ibSmNodeInfoNumPorts
ibSmNodeInfoNumPorts.description: Number of physical ports on this node.

ibSmNodeInfoSystemImageGUID.name: ibSmNodeInfoSystemImageGUID
ibSmNodeInfoSystemImageGUID.description: GUID associating this node with other nodes controlled by common supervisory code. Provides a means for system software to indicate the availability of multiple paths to the same destination via multiple nodes. All zero indicates that node association is not desired. The SystemImageGUID may be the NodeGUID of one of the associated nodes if that node is not field-replaceable.

ibSmNodeInfoPartitionCap.name: ibSmNodeInfoPartitionCap
ibSmNodeInfoPartitionCap.description: Number of entries in the partition table for CA, router, and the switch management port. This is at a minimum set to 1 for all nodes including switch.

ibSmNodeInfoDeviceID.name: ibSmNodeInfoDeviceID
ibSmNodeInfoDeviceID.description: Device ID information as assigned by device manufacturer.

ibSmNodeInfoVendorID.name: ibSmNodeInfoVendorID
ibSmNodeInfoVendorID.description: Device vendor ID, per IEEE. see www.standards.ieee.org/regauth/oui/oui.txt for details.

ibSmNodeInfoDescription.name: ibSmNodeInfoDescription
ibSmNodeInfoDescription.description: A vendor specific optional text string describing this node.

ibSmPortInfoTable.name: ibSmPortInfoTable
ibSmPortInfoTable.description: A table used to list all IB ports that are actively managed by the Subnet Managers on this device.

ibSmPortInfoSubnetPrefix.name: ibSmPortInfoSubnetPrefix
ibSmPortInfoSubnetPrefix.description: Subnet prefix of this IB subnet.

ibSmPortInfoNodeGUID.name: ibSmPortInfoNodeGUID
ibSmPortInfoNodeGUID.description: The 64-bit GUID of the node that contains this port.

ibSmPortInfoPortNum.name: ibSmPortInfoPortNum
ibSmPortInfoPortNum.description: The port number of this port.

ibSmPortInfoMKey.name: ibSmPortInfoMKey
ibSmPortInfoMKey.description: The 64-bit management Key for this port.

ibSmPortInfoGIDPrefix.name: ibSmPortInfoGIDPrefix
ibSmPortInfoGIDPrefix.description: The 64-bit GID prefix for this port.

ibSmPortInfoLID.name: ibSmPortInfoLID
ibSmPortInfoLID.description: The 16-bit base LID of this port.

ibSmPortInfoMasterSmLID.name: ibSmPortInfoMasterSmLID
ibSmPortInfoMasterSmLID.description: The 16-bit base LID of the master SM that is managing this port.

ibSmPortInfoCapMask.name: ibSmPortInfoCapMask
ibSmPortInfoCapMask.description: Supported capabilities of this node. A bit set to 1 for affirmation of supported capability: 0: Reserved, shall be zero 1: IsSM 2: IsNoticeSupported 3: IsTrapSupported 4: IsResetSupported 5: IsAutomaticMigrationSupported 6: IsSLMappingSupported 7: IsMKeyNVRAM 8: IsPKeyNVRAM 9: IsLEDInfoSupported 10: IsSMDisabled 11: IsSystemImageGUIDSuppported 12: IsPKeySwitchExternalPortTrapSupported 13-15: Reserved, shall be zero 16: IsConnectionManagerSupported 17: IsSNMPTunnelingSupported 18: Reserved, shall be zero 19: IsDeviceManagementSupported 20: IsVendorClassSupported 21: IsDRNoticeSupported, 22: IsCapabilityMaskNoticeSupported 23: IsBootManagementSupported(23), 24-31: Reserved, shall be zero

ibSmPortInfoDiagCode.name: ibSmPortInfoDiagCode
ibSmPortInfoDiagCode.description: Diagnostic code: Bits 3-0: 0x0: Port Ready; 0x1: Performing Self Test; 0x2: Initializing; 0x3: soft error - port has a non-fatal error and may be used; 0x4: hard error -port may not be used; 0x5-0xF: Reserved. Bits 14-4: for vender specific information.

ibSmPortInfoMKeyLeasePeriod.name: ibSmPortInfoMKeyLeasePeriod
ibSmPortInfoMKeyLeasePeriod.description: Specifies the initial value of the lease period timer in seconds. It's the length of time that the M_Key Protection bits are to remain non zero after a SubnSet(PortInfo) fails a M_Key check.

ibSmPortInfoLinkWidthEnabled.name: ibSmPortInfoLinkWidthEnabled
ibSmPortInfoLinkWidthEnabled.description: Enabled link width. Indicated as follows: 0: No state change; 1: 1x; 2: 4x; 3: 1x or 4x; 8: 12x; 9: 1x or 12x; 10: 4x or 12x; 11: 1x, 4x or 12x; 1-7, 12-254: reserved; 255: Set to ibSmPortInfoLinkWidthSupported value.

ibSmPortInfoLinkWidthSupported.name: ibSmPortInfoLinkWidthSupported
ibSmPortInfoLinkWidthSupported.description: Supported link width. Indicated as follows: 1: 1x; 3: 1x or 4x; 11: 1x, 4x or 12x; other values reserved.

ibSmPortInfoLinkWidthActive.name: ibSmPortInfoLinkWidthActive
ibSmPortInfoLinkWidthActive.description: Currently active link width. Indicated as follows: 1: 1x; 2: 4x; 8: 12x; other values reserved.

ibSmPortInfoLinkSpeedSupported.name: ibSmPortInfoLinkSpeedSupported
ibSmPortInfoLinkSpeedSupported.description: Supported link speed. Indicated as follows: 1: 2.5Gps; other values reserved.

ibSmPortInfoState.name: ibSmPortInfoState
ibSmPortInfoState.description: Port state. When writing to this field, only legal transitions are valid: 0: noStateChange; 1: down; 2: initialize; 3: armed; 4: active; 5: reserved.

ibSmPortInfoPhyState.name: ibSmPortInfoPhyState
ibSmPortInfoPhyState.description: When writing this field, only legal transition are valid. noStateChange(0), sleep(1), polling(2), disabled(3), portConfigurationTraining(4), linkup(5),linkErrorRecovery(6), reserved(7).

ibSmPortInfoLinkDownDefState.name: ibSmPortInfoLinkDownDefState
ibSmPortInfoLinkDownDefState.description: When writing this field, only legal transitions are valid. noStateChange(0), sleep(1), polling(2), reserved(3)

ibSmPortInfoMKeyProtBits.name: ibSmPortInfoMKeyProtBits
ibSmPortInfoMKeyProtBits.description: The bits are described below: 0: SubnGet() shall succeed for any Key in the MADHeader:M_Key and SubnGetResp(PortInfo) shall return the contents of the PortInfo:M_Key component. 1: SubnGet() shall succeed for any Key in the MADHeader:M_Key and SubnGetResp(PortInfo) shall return the contents of the PortInfo:M_Key component set to zero if MADHeader:M_Key does not match the PortInfo:M Key component of the port. 2: SubnGet() and SubnSet() shall fail if MADHeader:M_Key does not match the PortInfo:M_Key component in the port. 3: SubnGet() and SubnSet() shall fail if MADHeader:M_Key does not match the PortInfo:M_Key component in the port.

ibSmPortInfoLMC.name: ibSmPortInfoLMC
ibSmPortInfoLMC.description: LID mask for multipath support. User should take extra caution when setting this value, since any change will effect packet routing.

ibSmPortInfoLinkSpeedActive.name: ibSmPortInfoLinkSpeedActive
ibSmPortInfoLinkSpeedActive.description: Current active link speed, indicated as follows: 1: 2.5Gps; other values reserved.

ibSmPortInfoLinkSpeedEnabled.name: ibSmPortInfoLinkSpeedEnabled
ibSmPortInfoLinkSpeedEnabled.description: Enabled link speed, indicated as follows: 0: No state change; 1: 2.5Gps; 2-14: reserved; 15: Set to ibSmPortLinkSpeedSupported value. When writing this field only legal transitions are valid.

ibSmPortInfoNeighborMTU.name: ibSmPortInfoNeighborMTU
ibSmPortInfoNeighborMTU.description: Active maximum MTU enabled on this port for transmit. 1: 256; 2: 512; 3: 1024; 4: 2048; 5: 4096

ibSmPortInfoMasterSmSL.name: ibSmPortInfoMasterSmSL
ibSmPortInfoMasterSmSL.description: The administrative SL of the master SM that is managing this port.

ibSmPortInfoVLCap.name: ibSmPortInfoVLCap
ibSmPortInfoVLCap.description: Virtual Lanes supported on this port: 1:VL0, 2:VL0-VL1, 3:VL0-VL3, 4:VL0-VL7, 5:VL0-VL14, 0, 6-15: reserved.

ibSmPortInfoVLHighLimit.name: ibSmPortInfoVLHighLimit
ibSmPortInfoVLHighLimit.description: Limit of high priority component of VL arbitration table.

ibSmPortInfoVLArbHighCap.name: ibSmPortInfoVLArbHighCap
ibSmPortInfoVLArbHighCap.description: VL/Weight pairs supported on this port in the smVLArbTable for high priority.

ibSmPortInfoVLArbLowCap.name: ibSmPortInfoVLArbLowCap
ibSmPortInfoVLArbLowCap.description: VL/Weight pairs supported on this port in the smVLArbTable for low priority.

ibSmPortInfoMTUCap.name: ibSmPortInfoMTUCap
ibSmPortInfoMTUCap.description: Maximum MTU supported by this port: 1: 256; 2: 512; 3: 1024; 4: 2048; 5: 4096

ibSmPortInfoVLStallCount.name: ibSmPortInfoVLStallCount
ibSmPortInfoVLStallCount.description: Specifies the number of sequential packets dropped that causes the port to enter the VLStalled state.

ibSmPortInfoHOQLife.name: ibSmPortInfoHOQLife
ibSmPortInfoHOQLife.description: Sets the time a packet can live at the head of a VL queue.

ibSmPortInfoOperVL.name: ibSmPortInfoOperVL
ibSmPortInfoOperVL.description: Virtual Lanes operational on this port: 1:VL0, 2:VL0-VL1, 3:VL0-VL3, 4:VL0-VL7, 5:VL0-VL14, 0, 6-15: reserved.

ibSmPortInfoInPartEnforce.name: ibSmPortInfoInPartEnforce
ibSmPortInfoInPartEnforce.description: Indicates support of optional partition enforcement on packets received from this port.

ibSmPortInfoOutPartEnforce.name: ibSmPortInfoOutPartEnforce
ibSmPortInfoOutPartEnforce.description: Indicates support of optional partition enforcement on packets transmitted from this port.

ibSmPortInfoInFilterRawPktEnf.name: ibSmPortInfoInFilterRawPktEnf
ibSmPortInfoInFilterRawPktEnf.description: Indicates support of optional raw packet enforcement on raw packets received from this port.

ibSmPortInfoOutFilterRawPktEnf.name: ibSmPortInfoOutFilterRawPktEnf
ibSmPortInfoOutFilterRawPktEnf.description: Indicates support of optional raw packet enforcement on raw packets transmitted from this port.

ibSmPortInfoMKeyViolation.name: ibSmPortInfoMKeyViolation
ibSmPortInfoMKeyViolation.description: Counts the number of SMP packets that have been received on the port that have had invalid M_Key, since power on or reset. Increments till count reaches all 1s and then must be set back to zero to re-able incrementing.

ibSmPortInfoPKeyViolation.name: ibSmPortInfoPKeyViolation
ibSmPortInfoPKeyViolation.description: Counts the number of packets that have been received on the port that have had invalid P_Key, since power on or reset. Increments till count reaches all 1s and then must be set back to zero to re-able incrementing.

ibSmPortInfoQKeyViolation.name: ibSmPortInfoQKeyViolation
ibSmPortInfoQKeyViolation.description: Counts the number of packets that have been received on the port that have had invalid Q_Key, since power on or reset. Increments till count reaches all 1s and then must be set back to zero to re-able incrementing.

ibSmPortInfoGUIDCap.name: ibSmPortInfoGUIDCap
ibSmPortInfoGUIDCap.description: Number of GUID entries supported in the GUIDInfo attribute for this port.

ibSmPortInfoSubnetTimeout.name: ibSmPortInfoSubnetTimeout
ibSmPortInfoSubnetTimeout.description: Specifies the maximum expected subnet propagation delay, which depends upon the configuration of the switches, to reach any other port in the subnet and shall also be used to determine the maximum rate which SubnTraps() can be sent from this port. The duration of time is calculated based on (4.096 microsecond * 2 ^ object value)

ibSmPortInfoRespTime.name: ibSmPortInfoRespTime
ibSmPortInfoRespTime.description: Specifies the expected maximum time between the port reception of a SMP and the transmission of the associated response. The duration of time is calculated based on (4.096 microsecond * 2 ^ object value)

ibSmPortInfoLocalPhyError.name: ibSmPortInfoLocalPhyError
ibSmPortInfoLocalPhyError.description: Threshold value. When the count of marginal link errors exceeds this threshold, the local link integrity error shall be generated.

ibSmPortInfoOverrunError.name: ibSmPortInfoOverrunError
ibSmPortInfoOverrunError.description: Threshold value. When the count of buffer overruns over consecutive flow control update periods exceeds this threshold, the excessive buffer overrun error shall be generated.

ibSmPortInfoInitType.name: ibSmPortInfoInitType
ibSmPortInfoInitType.description: Optional; shall be 0 if not implemented. Type of initialization requested by this port before SM moves it to Active or Armed state. Bit 0: NoLoad. 0 = Port is requesting that its attributes be initialized. 1 = Port is requesting that no data be loaded into its attributes at all, asserting that the last-loaded data still exists and is valid. Bit 1: PreserveContent. 0 = Port makes no request regarding content of the data that is loaded into its attributes. 1 = Port is requesting that all such data, if loaded, be set to the most recent content loaded by the SM. Bit 2: PreservePresence. 0 = Port is requesting that all settable SA attributes referencing this port be removed prior to activating this port and Report()s of in/out of service (trap numbers 64/65) be sent. 1 = Port is requesting that all such data be preserved, and Report()s of in/out of service (trap numbers 64/65) not be sent for this port. Bit 3: DoNotResuscitate. 0 = bits 0, 1, and 2 of this field are valid; initialization of this port should begin based on their values. 1 = bits 0, 1, and 2 are not valid; port is requesting that reinitialization of this port, and any Report()s of in/out of service (trap numbers 64/65) be delayed until this bit is set to 0. Other Bits: Reserved.

ibSmPortInfoInitTypeReply.name: ibSmPortInfoInitTypeReply
ibSmPortInfoInitTypeReply.description: Written by the SM prior to changing the port to Active or Armed state. Optional; shall be set to all 0s if not implemented. Indicates the type of initialization performed. Bit 0: NoLoadReply. 0 = Port attributes were initialized. 1 = No data was loaded into the port attributes. Bit 1: PreserveContentReply. 0 = No information is available regarding content of the data loaded into the port attributes. 1 = The data loaded into the port attributes was set to the content most recently loaded by the SM. Bit 2: PreservePresenceReply. 0 = All settable SA attributes referencing this port were removed prior to activating this port and Report()s of in/out of service (trap numbers 64/65) were sent. 1 = All such data existing when this port was last active was not removed and Report()s of in/out of service (trap numbers 64/65) were not sent. Other Bits: Reserved.

ibSmSwitchInfoTable.name: ibSmSwitchInfoTable
ibSmSwitchInfoTable.description: A table used to list all IB switches that are actively managed by the Subnet Managers on this device.

ibSmSwitchInfoSubnetPrefix.name: ibSmSwitchInfoSubnetPrefix
ibSmSwitchInfoSubnetPrefix.description: Subnet prefix of this IB subnet.

ibSmSwitchInfoLinearFdbCap.name: ibSmSwitchInfoLinearFdbCap
ibSmSwitchInfoLinearFdbCap.description: Number of entries supported in the Linear Unicast Forwarding table. Zero indicates that there is no Linear Forwarding Database.

ibSmSwitchInfoRandomFdbCap.name: ibSmSwitchInfoRandomFdbCap
ibSmSwitchInfoRandomFdbCap.description: Number of entries supported in the Random Unicast Forwarding table. Zero indicates that there is no Random Forwarding Database.

ibSmSwitchInfoMcastFdbCap.name: ibSmSwitchInfoMcastFdbCap
ibSmSwitchInfoMcastFdbCap.description: Number of entries supported in the Multicast Forwarding table.

ibSmSwitchInfoLinearFdbTop.name: ibSmSwitchInfoLinearFdbTop
ibSmSwitchInfoLinearFdbTop.description: Indicates the top of the linear forwarding table. Packets received with unicast DLIDs greater than this value are discarded by the switch. This component applies only to switches that implement linear forwarding tables and is ignored by switches that implement random forwarding tables.

ibSmSwitchInfoDefaultPort.name: ibSmSwitchInfoDefaultPort
ibSmSwitchInfoDefaultPort.description: Forward to this port all the unicast packets from the other ports whose DLID does not exist in the random forwarding table.

ibSmSwitchInfoDefPriMcastPort.name: ibSmSwitchInfoDefPriMcastPort
ibSmSwitchInfoDefPriMcastPort.description: Forward to this port all the multicast packets from the other ports whose DLID does not exist in the forwarding table.

ibSmSwitchInfoDefNonPriMcastPort.name: ibSmSwitchInfoDefNonPriMcastPort
ibSmSwitchInfoDefNonPriMcastPort.description: Forward to this port all the multicast packets from the smDefPriMcastPort port whose DLID does not exist in the forwarding table.

ibSmSwitchInfoLifeTimeValue.name: ibSmSwitchInfoLifeTimeValue
ibSmSwitchInfoLifeTimeValue.description: The time a packet can live in the switch.

ibSmSwitchInfoPortStateChange.name: ibSmSwitchInfoPortStateChange
ibSmSwitchInfoPortStateChange.description: It is set to PortInTransition(1) anytime the PortState component in the PortInfo of any ports transition from Down to Initialize, Initialize to Down, Armed to Down, or Active to Down as a result of link state machine logic: 0: portNotInTransition; 1: portInTransition.

ibSmSwitchInfoLIDsPerPort.name: ibSmSwitchInfoLIDsPerPort
ibSmSwitchInfoLIDsPerPort.description: Number of LID/LMC combinations that may be assigned to a given external port for switches that support the random forwarding table.

ibSmSwitchInfoPartitionEnfCap.name: ibSmSwitchInfoPartitionEnfCap
ibSmSwitchInfoPartitionEnfCap.description: The number of entries in this partition enforcement table per physical port. Zero indicates that partition enforcement is not supported by the switch

ibSmSwitchInfoInEnfCap.name: ibSmSwitchInfoInEnfCap
ibSmSwitchInfoInEnfCap.description: Indicates switch is capable of partition enforcement on received packets.

ibSmSwitchInfoOutEnfCap.name: ibSmSwitchInfoOutEnfCap
ibSmSwitchInfoOutEnfCap.description: Indicates switch is capable of partition enforcement on transmitted packets.

ibSmSwitchInfoInFilterRawPktCap.name: ibSmSwitchInfoInFilterRawPktCap
ibSmSwitchInfoInFilterRawPktCap.description: Indicates switch is capable of raw packet enforcement on received packets.

ibSmSwitchInfoOutFilterRawPktCap.name: ibSmSwitchInfoOutFilterRawPktCap
ibSmSwitchInfoOutFilterRawPktCap.description: Indicates switch is capable of raw packet enforcement on transmitted packets.

ibSmSwitchInfoEnhanced0.name: ibSmSwitchInfoEnhanced0
ibSmSwitchInfoEnhanced0.description: Indicates whether switch port 0 supports enhanced functions.

ibSmPartitionTable.name: ibSmPartitionTable
ibSmPartitionTable.description: A table used to list all partitions that are managed by the Subnet Managers on this device.

ibSmPartitionSubnetPrefix.name: ibSmPartitionSubnetPrefix
ibSmPartitionSubnetPrefix.description: Subnet prefix of this IB subnet.

ibSmPartitionKey.name: ibSmPartitionKey
ibSmPartitionKey.description: The 16-bit P-Key of this Partition entry.

ibSmPartitionVectorIndex.name: ibSmPartitionVectorIndex
ibSmPartitionVectorIndex.description: An index indentifying a particular vector of the partition table.

ibSmPartitionVector.name: ibSmPartitionVector
ibSmPartitionVector.description: A vector containing a portion of the partition table. To retrieve the entire table, the user must perform consecutive GET operations to read one vector at a time.

ibSmPartitionVectorSize.name: ibSmPartitionVectorSize
ibSmPartitionVectorSize.description: Indicates the size (in bytes) of the current vector.

ibSmPartitionVectorElementSize.name: ibSmPartitionVectorElementSize
ibSmPartitionVectorElementSize.description: Indicates the size (in bytes) of each element in the vector. Each GET operation on the 'ibSmPartitionVector' variable will return zero or more elements. Each element is ten(10) bytes long. This is how the ten bytes are coded (in network byte order): byte description ---- ----------- 1-8 Node-GUID of the member 9 Port number (0..255) 10 Partition type (1=full-membership, 2=limited-membership) The number of elements in 'ibSmPartitionVector' can be calculated by dividing 'ibSmPartitionVectorSize' by 'ibSmPartitionVectorElementSize'.

ibSmPartitionLastChange.name: ibSmPartitionLastChange
ibSmPartitionLastChange.description: Indicates the time stamp when the partition table was last changed. To verify the entire partition table was read without any changes to the table in between GET operations, the user can do a comparion on this time stamp.

ibSmPartitionConfigSubnetPrefix.name: ibSmPartitionConfigSubnetPrefix
ibSmPartitionConfigSubnetPrefix.description: Subnet prefix of an IB subnet.

ibSmPartitionConfigKey.name: ibSmPartitionConfigKey
ibSmPartitionConfigKey.description: The 16-bit P-Key of an IB partition.

ibSmPartitionConfigAction.name: ibSmPartitionConfigAction
ibSmPartitionConfigAction.description: Used to specify an action to perform on a specified IB Subnet Partition.

ibSmPartitionConfigMemberNodeGUID.name: ibSmPartitionConfigMemberNodeGUID
ibSmPartitionConfigMemberNodeGUID.description: Used to specify the Node GUID of a member.

ibSmPartitionConfigMemberPortNum.name: ibSmPartitionConfigMemberPortNum
ibSmPartitionConfigMemberPortNum.description: Used to specify the local port number of a member.

ibSmPartitionConfigMemberType.name: ibSmPartitionConfigMemberType
ibSmPartitionConfigMemberType.description: Used to specify the type of membership of a member.

ibSmMcastGroupTable.name: ibSmMcastGroupTable
ibSmMcastGroupTable.description: A table used to list all multicast groups actively managed by the Subnet Managers on this device.

ibSmMcastGroupSubnetPrefix.name: ibSmMcastGroupSubnetPrefix
ibSmMcastGroupSubnetPrefix.description: Subnet prefix of this IB subnet.

ibSmMcastGroupMGID.name: ibSmMcastGroupMGID
ibSmMcastGroupMGID.description: The 128-bit multicast GID address for this multicast group.

ibSmMcastGroupQKey.name: ibSmMcastGroupQKey
ibSmMcastGroupQKey.description: The 16-bit Q-Key of this multicast group.

ibSmMcastGroupMLID.name: ibSmMcastGroupMLID
ibSmMcastGroupMLID.description: The 16-bit LID of this multicast group.

ibSmMcastGroupMTU.name: ibSmMcastGroupMTU
ibSmMcastGroupMTU.description: The MTU of this multicast group: 1: 256; 2: 512; 3: 1024; 4: 2048; 5: 4096

ibSmMcastGroupTClass.name: ibSmMcastGroupTClass
ibSmMcastGroupTClass.description: The Tclass to be used in the GRH if GRH is used.

ibSmMcastGroupPKey.name: ibSmMcastGroupPKey
ibSmMcastGroupPKey.description: The 16-bit Partition Key for this multicast group.

ibSmMcastGroupRate.name: ibSmMcastGroupRate
ibSmMcastGroupRate.description: Traffic rate of this multicast group: 2: 2.5 Gb/sec; 3: 10 Gb/sec; 4: 30 Gb/sec; 0, 1, 5-63: reserved.

ibSmMcastGroupPacketLifeTime.name: ibSmMcastGroupPacketLifeTime
ibSmMcastGroupPacketLifeTime.description: Packet life time of this multicast group.

ibSmMcastGroupSL.name: ibSmMcastGroupSL
ibSmMcastGroupSL.description: Service level of this multicast group.

ibSmMcastGroupFlowLabel.name: ibSmMcastGroupFlowLabel
ibSmMcastGroupFlowLabel.description: Flow label to be used on this multicast group if GRH Is used.

ibSmMcastGroupHopLimit.name: ibSmMcastGroupHopLimit
ibSmMcastGroupHopLimit.description: Hop limit to be used on this multicast group if GRH Is used.

ibSmMcastGroupScope.name: ibSmMcastGroupScope
ibSmMcastGroupScope.description: Scope of this multicast group: 2: link local; 5: site local; 8: organization local; 14: global; other values reserved.

ibSmMcastMemberTable.name: ibSmMcastMemberTable
ibSmMcastMemberTable.description: A table used to list all members of multicast groups managed by the Subnet Managers on this device.

ibSmMcastMemberSubnetPrefix.name: ibSmMcastMemberSubnetPrefix
ibSmMcastMemberSubnetPrefix.description: Subnet prefix of this IB subnet.

ibSmMcastMemberMGID.name: ibSmMcastMemberMGID
ibSmMcastMemberMGID.description: The 128-bit multicast GID address for this multicast group.

ibSmMcastMemberVectorIndex.name: ibSmMcastMemberVectorIndex
ibSmMcastMemberVectorIndex.description: An index indentifying a particular vector of the multicast member table.

ibSmMcastMemberVector.name: ibSmMcastMemberVector
ibSmMcastMemberVector.description: A vector containing a portion of the multicast member table. To retrieve the entire table, the user must perform consecutive GET operations to read one vector at a time.

ibSmMcastMemberVectorSize.name: ibSmMcastMemberVectorSize
ibSmMcastMemberVectorSize.description: Indicates the size (in bytes) of the current vector.

ibSmMcastMemberVectorElementSize.name: ibSmMcastMemberVectorElementSize
ibSmMcastMemberVectorElementSize.description: Indicates the size (in bytes) of each element in the vector. Each GET operation on the 'ibSmMcastMemberVector' variable will return zero or more elements. Each element is eighteen(18) bytes long. This is how the eighteen bytes are coded (in network byte order): byte description ---- ----------- 1-16 Member port GID 17 Member join state (bitmask bit 0=fullMember, bit 1=nonMember, bit 2=sendOnlyMember) 18 Member proxy join status (1=true, 2=false) The number of elements in 'ibSmMcastMemberVector' can be calculated by dividing 'ibSmMcastMemberVectorSize' by 'ibSmMcastMemberVectorElementSize'.

ibSmMcastMemberLastChange.name: ibSmMcastMemberLastChange
ibSmMcastMemberLastChange.description: Indicates the time stamp when the multicast member table was last changed. To verify the entire table was read without any changes to the table in between GET operations, the user can do a comparison on this time stamp.
